summary: This document is a chain of email correspondence from June 2020 between the FBI's New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking Task Force and Expedia's Law Enforcement Request team regarding a subpoena for records related to Ghislaine Maxwell. The emails show the FBI attempting to obtain booking information using email addresses, but Expedia reports finding no records and eventually closes the request due to lack of follow-up information.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The entire email chain concerns an FBI subpoena to Expedia for records related to Ghislaine Maxwell, specifically seeking booking information associated with her email addresses.

events.title: FBI serves subpoena on Expedia for Maxwell records
events.description: The FBI serves a subpoena on Expedia seeking booking records related to Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Expedia-FBI correspondence regarding Maxwell subpoena
events.description: A series of emails between Expedia's Law Enforcement Request team and an FBI Special Agent where Expedia requests more identifying information (email addresses, credit card numbers) to search for Maxwell's records, reports finding no bookings with the provided emails, and ultimately closes the request after 30 days of no response.

events.title: Internal FBI forwarding of Expedia correspondence
events.description: An FBI contractor forwards the email chain with Expedia regarding the closed Maxwell records request to another party, noting it is for a spreadsheet and file sharing.

locations: New York, NY (FBI New York Field Office)
Bellevue, WA 98004, USA (Expedia Law Enforcement Request office at 333 108th Avenue NE)
keyFacts: The FBI's New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking Task Force was actively seeking Ghislaine Maxwell's travel booking records from Expedia via subpoena in early 2020.
Expedia's records system required specific identifiers like email addresses or credit card numbers, not just a name and date of birth, to locate customer bookings.
Expedia reported to the FBI that searches using the provided email addresses for Ghislaine Maxwell returned no booking records.
The FBI's request for records was closed by Expedia in March 2020 due to the FBI not providing additional identifying information within a 30-day window.
The correspondence was marked as 'Confidential' and was internally forwarded within the FBI in June 2020 for record-keeping in a spreadsheet.
